The paper deals with privacy-preserving machine learning algorithms, specifically for estimating Generalized Linear Models (GLM) and non-linear regression in the Non-interactive Local Differential Privacy (NLDP) model. This falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as well as Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses techniques from Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) to analyze the sample complexity of the algorithms. Finally, the paper includes experiments on real-world datasets, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
